      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "An unknown hydrocarbon <b>A</b> with the formula C<sub>6</sub>H<sub>12</sub> reacts with 1 molar equivalent of H<sub>2</sub> over a palladium catalyst. Hydrocarbon <b>A</b> also reacts with OsO<sub>4</sub> to give diol <b>B</b>. When oxidized with KMnO<sub>4</sub> in acidic solution, <b>A</b> gives two fragments. One fragment is propanoic acid, CH<sub>3</sub>CH<sub>2</sub>CO<sub>2</sub>H, and the other fragment is ketone <b>C</b>. What are the structures of <b>A</b>, <b>B</b>, and <b>C</b>? Write all reactions.",
